BLOCKING BUGS (Prioritized)
B1 — Sign Out infinite redirect loop (CRITICAL)
Clicking "Sign Out" navigates via GET to /api/auth/signout, which requires a POST. The page enters an exponentially-growing callbackUrl redirect loop that renders the browser tab unresponsive. Users cannot log out via the UI. Fix: Replace the <a href="/api/auth/signout"> link with a form or button that posts to NextAuth's signout endpoint (e.g., signOut() from next-auth/react).
B2 — Login/Register form never shows error messages (HIGH)
The Sign In, Register, and (by extension) all auth forms silently discard server errors. Wrong password, invalid domain, short password — none produce visible feedback. The API returns correct error codes and messages (verified via direct calls), but the UI form simply resets. Fix: Handle the error response from signIn() / the register API and set it into component state for display.
B3 — Comment body text not rendered (HIGH)
Posted comments appear with only the author name and relative timestamp. The comment content itself is absent from the rendered DOM. Fix: Check the comments rendering component — the content field is likely not being passed to the template or is being mapped to the wrong key.
B4 — Discard button does not revert (MEDIUM)
Clicking "Discard" on the task detail panel does not restore the previously saved field values — the unsaved changes remain. Fix: The Discard handler should reset the local form state back to the last-fetched server values.
B5 — Delete task has no confirmation dialog (MEDIUM)
Clicking the "Delete" button in the task panel header immediately deletes the task with no confirmation prompt. In a HIPAA context with important task data, irreversible actions should require confirmation. Fix: Add a modal confirm step ("Are you sure you want to delete this task?").

